definition.value: The capital of Paraguay. The city sits on the left bank of the Paraguay River, which separates the city in the north-west from the Occidental Region of Paraguay and Argentina in the south part of the city. The rest of the city is surrounded by the Central Department.
A district located in south-central Bangladesh.
One of the six administrative divisions of Bangladesh. It covers the most southern areas of the country.

One of the six divisions of Bangladesh and is located in the south-west of the country. The Khulna Division borders the Rajshahi Division to the north, the Dhaka Division to the north-east, Barisal Division to the east, the Bay of Bengal to the south and the State of West Bengal (in India) to the west. Barisal Division was formerly part of Khulna Division.

One of the six administrative divisions of Bangladesh. Rajshahi Division is in the north western corner of Bangladesh. The river Padma borders Rajshahi Division on the south and another river, Jamuna, lies across the eastern border. In the North and West, Rajshahi Division shares a border with India.

The Northeastern division (bibhag) of Bangladesh, named after its main city, Sylhet. It is bounded by Meghalaya State of India on the north, Tripura State on the south, Assam State of India on the east and Dhaka and Chittagong divisions on the west.
The capital of Pakistan, and is located in the Potohar Plateau in the north of the country, within the Islamabad Capital Territory.
The capital of Assam, a state in northeast India. Dispur is part of Gauhati (Lok Sabha constituency).
A city.
The capital of the Indian State of Goa. It lies on the banks of the Mandovi estuary, in the district of North Goa.
The capital of Gujarat State, India. Located on the banks of the River Sabarmati, the city is the administrative centre of Gandhinagar District.
A census town in the Indian Union Territory of Lakshadweep.
A populated place. A city in the State of Maharashtra in India.
A large city in central India.
A populated place. A town in the district of Nandurbar.
A populated place. A village in the State of Maharashtra, India.
A subdistrict of Yavatmal District.
The capital of the Indian State of Manipur.
The capital of Meghalaya, one of the smallest states in India. It is also the district headquarters of the East Khasi Hills District.
The largest city as well as the capital of the State of Mizoram in India.
The capital of Nagaland.
The capital and largest city of the Indian State of Orissa, India.
A city located in the northwestern tip of the Indian State of Orissa at the heart of a rich mineral belt.
The capital and largest town of the Indian State of Sikkim. Gangtok is located in the Shivalik Hills of the eastern Himalayan range.
A populated place. A city in the Vellore district in the Indian State of Tamil Nadu.
The capital of the Indian State of Tripura. It lies on the Haora River and is located 2 km from Bangladesh.

A populated place. A city in the Indian State of West Bengal. It is located in the Siliguri Corridor or Chicken's Neck, the very narrow strip of land linking mainland India to its north eastern states.
The capital of the Indian State of Bihar. Patna lies on the southern bank of the Ganges.
The capital city of the State of Chhattisgarh, India. It was formerly a part of Madhya Pradesh before the State of Chhattisgarh was formed on 2000-11-01.
The capital city of Himachal Pradesh. Shimla is located in the north-western ranges of the Himalayas.
A populated place. The largest city in the Jammu region and the winter capital of the State of Jammu and Kashmir, India.
A populated place. A city in the valley of Kashmir that lies on both banks of the Jhelum River, a tributary of the Indus River.
The capital city of the Indian State of Jharkhand.
A populated place. A city in central India. It is the capital of the Indian State of Madhya Pradesh and the administrative headquarters of Bhopal District and Bhopal Division.
A populated place. A city in the State of Madhya Pradesh in India.
A small cantonment town in the Indore District of the Malwa region of Madhya Pradesh state, India.

A city. It is located to the West of Chandigarh. It is almost a continuation of Chandigarh. To its north is Rupnagar district. To its south are Fatehgarh Sahib and Patiala. Due to fast urban growth, Mohali has almost merged into the Chandigarh city.
A populated place. A city in Bareilly district in the northern Indian State of Uttar Pradesh. Standing on the Ramganga river.

The capital city of the State of Uttarakhand (earlier called Uttaranchal) in India, and the headquarters of Dehradun District. The district is surrounded by the Himalayas in the north, Shivalik Hills in the south, the river Ganga in the east, and the river Yamuna in the west. The water divide of Ganga and Yamuna passes through the city.
A populated place. A city in the Center District of Israel, north-east of Tel Aviv.
A religious kibbutz, located south of Kiryat Malakhi in south-central Israel. It is under the jurisdiction of Shafir Regional Council.
An Israeli town in the Sharon region. It is located east of Netanya and north of Kfar Saba.
